Lucas Industries Inc's convertibleeurobond has been increased to 83 mln dlrs from the initial 75mln dlrs due to strong demand for the deal, lead manager J.Henry Schroder Wagg and Co Ltd said.    The coupon has been set at 5-1/4 pct. The conversion priceis fixed at 640 pence per share, representing a premium of11-1/2 pct over yesterday's mid-price close of 574 pence.    The seven year put option was priced at 118 pct to give theinvestor a yield to the put of 7.31 pct. The foreign exchangerate was fixed at 1.6030 U.S. Dlrs to one stg. The borrower isa unit of Lucas Industries Plc &lt;LUCS.L>. REUTER&#3;